---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import BubbleSimulator from '../components/BubbleSimulator';
---

<BaseLayout title="DLM (2005) Bubble Simulator — Josh">
  <div class="sim-page">
    <div class="sim-header">
      <h1>DLM (2005) — Bubbles and Experience</h1>
      <p class="sim-subtitle">
        Interactive replication of Dufwenberg, Lindqvist & Moore (AER 2005).
        SSW double auction with heterogeneous agents, experience-indexed belief updating, and round-4 novice replacement.
      </p>
    </div>

    <BubbleSimulator client:load />

    <div class="sim-footer">
      <details>
        <summary>About this simulation</summary>
        <div class="about-content">
          <p>
            Browser-based agent simulation of the SSW (Smith, Suchanek & Williams 1988)
            asset market as implemented by DLM (2005). Heterogeneous CRRA agents trade a
            <strong>single</strong> finite-lived asset over a sequence of four consecutive
            markets (rounds); there is no simultaneous multi-asset portfolio. Rounds 1–3 keep
            the same traders (who gain experience); at the replacement round a fraction of
            experienced traders is swapped out for inexperienced newcomers.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>The four conclusions this reproduces (calibrated to the reference
            implementation):</strong>
          </p>
          <ol>
            <li>Positive mispricing (a bubble) that <strong>decreases as players accumulate
              experience</strong> (rounds 1 → 3).</li>
            <li>A <strong>minority of experienced + majority of inexperienced</strong> traders
              do <strong>not</strong> generate large bubbles in the replacement round.</li>
            <li>The size of the mispricing <strong>depends on the asset type</strong>
              (linear-declining, perpetual, growth, cyclical, random-walk, jump/crash).</li>
            <li>Experience <strong>does not transfer across assets</strong>: when the
              replacement round swaps to a different asset, veterans' experience is discounted
              by how weakly the two assets' fundamentals correlate.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>


<style>
  .sim-page {
    padding: 1.5rem 1rem;
  }
  .sim-header {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .sim-header h1 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .sim-subtitle {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.5;
    max-width: 640px;
  }
  .sim-footer {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding-top: 1rem;
  }
  .sim-footer summary {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    cursor: pointer;
  }
  .about-content {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 640px;
  }
  .about-content p {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
</style>
